message: Hello, I am Ethnobot
\What's your name?\
Nick
Hi {previousValue}, nice to meet you!
What’s your Job?
External Relations, Edinburgh World Heritage
Today I want you to help with a specific strand of Research for the Edinburgh City Council’s Public art research Project.
You will take me on a curated experience involving three works of art; art that is transformative, contentious, and new.
Are you ready to get started?

The Witches' Well
What makes this work of art contentious? And for whom?
It is a memorial to those who were executed for witchcraft. It's controversial because of subject matter, but also because it's so small and the witch craze in Scotland was so large.
Anything else to add?
Yes
The style of art is controversial as it suggests that the 'witches' my actually have practiced supernatural activities, rather than just being the victims of superstition and prejudice

Could you list the agencies, parties and individuals that should be involved for placing a work of art here?

Museum, CEC, heritage organisations, local rwaidents
